The paper deals with the identification of dynamical properties and topology of structured interconnections of dynamical systems, which is a topic that falls under the field of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of measured data for identification, which involves statistical and machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of external excitation and disturbance signals, which are common in the field of neuroscience (cs.NE) and signal processing (cs.SI).
